Nearby library at woodlands. There's a cafe inside selling gelato and some drinks. Too bad outside food and drinks are not allowed.

Library is quiet and at lvl 3 is the kids section. Usually I bring my daughter here to borrow books and chill.

text.text: Great library but cleanliness needs a lot of work. The floors are always dirty, full dust and hair strands under the tables, in the mornings. Guess they don't do daily cleaning at all after closing time. Even the sofas have hair strands stuck at the corners of the seat.

text.text: Don’t let the entrance deceive you. From the outside it may look a small and simple library. The lib actually do have 4 stories, and each story has a vast collection of books. Unlike other libraries, Woodland library may have the largest space all with comfy sofa or study desk. It also have a cafe if you need a quick coffee fix. Kids area upstairs.

text.text: Convenient place to study. Relaxing and clean. The staff provided enough tables and chairs. But the only things is very limited socket to charge your laptop. It is better to fully charge your devices before come :)

text.text:
The National Libraries are always one of my favourite places to visit in Singapore. Free admission, free books, free air conditioning, free wifi, plenty of seats and clean toilets.

Woodlands Regional Library is one of the best, big with plenty of tables and seats for everyone. Kids can go to Level 4, the rest of us can enjoy some peace and quiet from level one to three.

One can also learn about digital fabrication tools (Make IT at Libraries) for free at Level three. An enjoyable place for everyone.

** Closed on Public Holidays
